      "summary": "You love helping others understand and respond to good news. You’re energised by questions and enjoy breaking down complex ideas into simple, relatable explanations. You can talk to a room full of skeptics or a friend over coffee and help them see the heart of the message. Whether writing a blog post or leading a small group, you communicate with warmth and clarity. You notice what people need to hear and adapt your approach accordingly, weaving stories, questions and analogies to bring truth home. This blend of clarity and passion makes you an instructor: you present truth in a way that invites people to explore and embrace it.",
      "designStory": {
        "freeIntroduction": "You love helping others understand and respond to good news. You’re energised by questions and enjoy breaking down complex ideas into simple, relatable explanations. You can talk to a room full of skeptics or a friend over coffee and help them see the heart of the message. Whether writing a blog post or leading a small group, you communicate with warmth and clarity. You notice what people need to hear and adapt your approach accordingly, weaving stories, questions and analogies to bring truth home. This blend of clarity and passion makes you an instructor: you present truth in a way that invites people to explore and embrace it.",
        "premiumExtension": "Teaching precision meets evangelistic passion in you. You present the gospel with clarity, passion and a knack for simplifying complex truths. In daily life you host Q&A nights, write articles that demystify faith and create accessible study guides. At home you share stories that spark curiosity; in your neighbourhood you organise discussion evenings where questions are welcomed; at work you facilitate training sessions that connect values to mission. You love learning as much as teaching; staying curious and flexible helps you keep your message fresh and relevant. You value authenticity and relationship, adjusting your style based on feedback and inviting others to co‑create learning experiences. High extraversion fuels your energy to engage, while conscientiousness and curiosity help you craft clear messages; together they make you a persuasive explainer who removes barriers and invites response.\nIn relationships you bring enthusiasm and knowledge. You are the friend who shares an article or analogy that sheds light on a dilemma; you love answering questions and pointing people toward hope. Because you enjoy explaining, you might dominate conversation; practising listening and asking questions ensures that people feel heard, not lectured.\nIn the workplace you thrive in roles that involve presenting, training or translating information. You simplify complex tasks, create engaging content and facilitate conversations that lead to understanding. You also like to help colleagues develop their own voice, encouraging them to share their stories with confidence. Guard against turning every interaction into a lesson; authenticity and relationship matter more than performance. Depend on the Holy Spirit rather than solely on intellect."
      },
